	title = {Facilitation of global change research in the tropics: science and data management},
	abstract = {To  date,  much  global  change  research  has  focused  on  temperate  and  polar  systems (Parmesan, 2006). However, it is becoming increasingly clear that even small changes in temperature and precipitation can have large consequences for organisms in the tropics (e.g. Clark, 2007). Since the mid-1970s, tropical regions have experienced a mean temperature
